  "prompt": "What should I do if my Lenovo G500s gets stuck at the Lenovo start screen?",
  "response": "If your Lenovo G500s is stuck at the Lenovo start screen, try these troubleshooting steps:\n\n1. Basic Troubleshooting:\n- Force restart by holding down the power button for 10-15 seconds\n- Unplug the power adapter and remove the battery (if removable)\n- Reconnect power and restart\n\n2. Boot Options:\n- Try booting in Safe Mode by pressing F8 during startup\n- Use recovery options to restore or reset the system\n- Access BIOS setup by pressing Enter or F2 during startup\n\n3. Hardware Checks:\n- Disconnect external devices\n- Check RAM and hard drive connections\n- Run hardware diagnostics if possible\n\n4. Software Solutions:\n- Perform a system restore to a previous working point\n- Use Windows startup repair\n- Reinstall or repair Windows operating system\n\n5. Advanced Options:\n- Reset BIOS to default settings\n- Check for malware or virus infections\n- Consider professional repair if problems persist\n\nIf these steps don't resolve the issue, contact Lenovo support or a professional technician for further assistance.",
